{"id": "ed049ae6-0691-4736-b9ad-8c0327e5144c", "value": "Includes streetscape plantings, boulevards, landscaped medians and plantings associated with a parcel or subdivision"}
{"id": "a8429240-a5d3-4507-82ee-3b71865cd9b2", "value": "Billboard originally used to advertise off-premise goods and services may now serve as on-premise advertisement"}
{"id": "473c2ede-5cde-41c2-9365-c6f31f780dcd", "value": "Original and unique feature associated with Post-War suburban planning and design"}
{"id": "8a1acca2-bfea-4d84-b706-0030b9253adf", "value": "May be located near major motion picture studios"}

{"id": "799e6ab0-8284-41e9-89aa-ddf446845bb0", "value": "A geographically definable area composed of multiple subdivisions and/or portions of subdivisions that were either by design or circumstance developed with mostly multi-family property types"}
{"id": "aeb341a1-97d3-44a2-84c6-cde9cedd764c", "value": "1949 Master Plan of Branch Administrative Centers"}

{"id": "a58376bf-45de-415d-80b4-0390a5682bb4", "value": "Stucco, brick, and wood exteriors, usually in combination"}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "8cc6b189-fd80-41ce-8dc5-552c63ed79fd", "value": "Retains the ability to convey historic appearance from the period of significance"}
{"id": "f7090dc9-bcb1-4c2f-bb46-9c3676cac3c8", "value": "May be a good example of design features, facilities or equipment distinctive to its design and use as a post office"}
{"id": "93f42d40-4cf6-4bd5-8f25-33bcfa82796f", "value": "Individual must be proven to have made an important contribution to the early settlement and development of Wilmington"}
{"id": "6e6a59c5-2376-4ce9-b3f4-f23a8e02630b", "value": "Generally triangulates on two sides facing opposing traffic with a central panel parallel to the street (though sometimes semicircular)"}
{"id": "3f525b88-882a-4175-aac8-328a39f74cc3", "value": "While the broader setting has most likely changed, the immediate setting of the property should remain intact"}
{"id": "4d9bcbe9-eb54-4522-90b9-5e074700f86f", "value": "Exemplifies the tenets of the late Victorian era and the Vernacular Cottage style"}
{"id": "bc044ea7-1031-4699-bf29-5d0865c401d2", "value": "Is associated with Los Angeles Gas and Electric Corp., Bureau of Power and Light or the Department of Water and Power"}
{"id": "6e7e028d-9810-4f30-8d5e-488ecc55fbe5", "value": "Expression often whimisical or fanciful, featuring an unusual directness of execution that might seem naive or unschooled"}
{"id": "17fd1215-e9c3-40cb-aed2-9cf229388fe8", "value": "May be the original site of a significant entertainment industry-related labor, professional, or trade organization"}
{"id": "2b8db529-fbe0-493c-9e15-b49ca366a093", "value": "Represents a resource dating from the pre-consolidation period of Barnes City"}
{"id": "00e070c4-84e5-4e7a-baa7-1a9ab70882e8", "value": "Is associated with persons who made important individual contributions to the history of Los Angeles"}
{"id": "3cfef60b-2abe-47b3-85cf-e755e051242f", "value": "Best represents the merchant builders contributions to important patterns of residential suburbanization"}
{"id": "ab87a629-f22c-446a-9e22-cf4e252a9acc", "value": "Designed in popular architectural styles of the day"}
{"id": "8df9fced-6c44-4562-acda-896c805815f8", "value": "Developed in conjunction with the establishment of a streetcar line"}

{"id": "55d9fd80-2527-4c43-a67b-b3193cf059ac", "value": "Unified entity with a significant concentration of residences designed in Late 19th Century styles including Eastlake, Queen Anne, Shingle, Richardsonian Romanesque and Classical/Neoclassical Revival"}
{"id": "a65a200f-8825-4bd1-b80b-ab0ed5196b7e", "value": "Is the long-term residence of a person significant in the history of the performing arts"}
{"id": "be3484ac-eaac-429e-b00b-268052997720", "value": "Represents a resource dating from the pre-consolidation period of Watts"}
{"id": "db3f187d-1449-4ad3-8dc7-d0b4b848d2a8", "value": "Buildings often mixed-use, with commercial offices and retails stores as well as garment factories"}
{"id": "c41e04b4-c5ac-4d6d-99d4-911cc2d6307b", "value": "Is an excellent example of the property type"}
{"id": "c7855d37-a0f3-4d93-87e2-c08a7f606f88", "value": "Dramatic rooflines, including butterfly, folded plate (zig-zag), dome and cantilever"}
{"id": "5e2fdb87-8d1c-4292-9adf-5e4a5826e782", "value": "Innovative use of local natural materials such as stone, shells and sand, often mixed with cement"}
{"id": "8c0cabb4-9674-4ac3-80a7-dd4678381184", "value": "Generally are residential in character to fit into the surrounding neighborhood"}
{"id": "28ccdcec-be87-4534-a0d3-6fe996b16ded", "value": "Primarily applied to restaurants, food stands, and retail stores"}
{"id": "2e0df2d3-2606-4af9-bb87-56e8e6e876d0", "value": "The exteriors are often unassuming to maintain the privacy of the artists"}
{"id": "6d557fbb-4efd-4f1c-8ef1-c65e95c62826", "value": "Security bars may have been added to lower story"}
{"id": "f6c7ed0f-958b-45e9-a508-6a2c6a9af826", "value": "Constructed of reinforced concrete, older examples may be timber-framed \"mill construction\""}
{"id": "99b28420-c7fe-454b-bb03-accc8ca4d7a7", "value": "Represents a critical component of Los Angeles' garment industry"}
{"id": "ec8c7379-e645-46a7-962f-13e0d8d16908", "value": "Large wrap-around and inset porches often featuring brick or stone"}
{"id": "81cee382-dd4b-482e-9b7d-1b1ca434844e", "value": "Is associated with an event or series of events important in the formation, settlement or development of San Pedro"}
{"id": "0899d5a2-6d81-4981-9171-0c20fdb7fbe8", "value": "Was custom-designed (as opposed to mass produced Ranch Houses)"}
{"id": "8d057251-8db9-411f-84d0-e118a6fa15d9", "value": "Was purpose-built by a company to house workers close to the place of employment"}
{"id": "191adaf6-3334-44cd-9190-0a4eec0dd221", "value": "Played a significant role in the social and/or cultural history of the neighborhood or region"}
{"id": "4678ed87-3cdc-4738-bb77-43f4501922df", "value": "Conveys an advertising message through adaptations in the building form itself"}
{"id": "7529a02b-c33e-4b67-b3e7-07f0a2655bd3", "value": "Associated vernacular agricultural landscape features may include a ranch house, corrals, irrigation features, tanks, pasture land"}
{"id": "c656e62d-0fe6-403c-ab02-1c691cf2a4f8", "value": "Glass skins are typically set in a Cartesian grid of small metal mullions"}
{"id": "abeccde5-339d-4438-a128-366922bfba27", "value": "May constitute an environment, in the sense that visitors are able to walk through the site and become surrounded by the work"}
{"id": "ca663aad-1050-4071-bfba-4092f3104548", "value": "Evokes commercial or architectural design ethos of its period through its typography and/or placement"}
{"id": "d572c69d-691a-4724-b573-5f659e5d54f9", "value": "Tubing and bulbs may be broken or missing, with only electrical sockets for electrodes remaining"}
{"id": "4289a706-125b-48e5-8a5f-afe473cbcc4e", "value": "Constructed between 1887 and 1955 as a bottling plant"}
{"id": "fa11e59e-8526-437f-bfe9-9e100d0cfd2b", "value": "Two or more stories; may be up to five or six stories"}
{"id": "c1edf8b8-0a83-4b3e-80bb-23972a13a0b1", "value": "If Japanese-influenced, then may have multi-gabled roofs or gables that peak at the apex and flare at the ends"}
{"id": "3d3cec1e-78b9-403a-8a03-84892a1b2d48", "value": "Is an excellent example of the Dutch Colonial Revival style"}
{"id": "9e4c2a69-b438-47f1-8208-b9bb528cb196", "value": "Exemplifies the character-defining features of the Byzantine Revival style"}
{"id": "859d64a0-4231-4e05-93a4-60f335b2f62f", "value": "Is directly associated with the productive life of a writer during his or her residency in Los Angeles"}
{"id": "e44edd06-0e63-47f6-8e21-ecb230ed0542", "value": "May be associated with groups important in Venice\u2019s early ethnic history"}
{"id": "6696fb2a-9673-45c2-a7a5-4cd72f856acb", "value": "Original feature associated with tract/subdivision planning and design"}
{"id": "f06861d1-1561-4f6b-b6b4-e78f5324b0a5", "value": "One or more buildings, unified in style and oriented toward each other"}
{"id": "e7fa52ba-f674-444d-aa04-0af470ea8835", "value": "Associated industry facilities may not be extant"}
{"id": "391b2687-fb09-42dd-8c69-8ca40adcfa1b", "value": "Full- or partial-width front porches, usually recessed"}
{"id": "9b431767-b813-4ca4-ba2e-32341fb04fa0", "value": "Individual must be proven to have played an important and influential role in the Gay Civil Rights Movement"}
{"id": "ada296e0-c0fd-4bc0-b421-9491871ad297", "value": "Typically six or more stories in height; may be up to fourteen"}
{"id": "af4231ee-953a-492c-a439-7091928a9a82", "value": "Represents a resource dating from the pre-consolidation period of Venice"}
{"id": "e34810f9-dce2-419b-bce8-3cfe8124cee0", "value": "Is associated with a fraternal organization that played a pivotal role in the social history of L.A. or a specific L.A. community"}

{"id": "36f3f773-601d-4058-bae2-ffa41406125a", "value": "Illumination may be external: metal signs with exposed bulbs, tubing, and electrical sockets; reflective metal surfaces illuminated by lighting either attached to the structure or aimed towards it from afar"}
{"id": "d34f11be-4323-4252-ba70-8c017e0d83b1", "value": "Is a good example of the Beaux Arts style"}
{"id": "5b703931-1999-45c5-ab22-d47034fcffaa", "value": "Is an excellent example of its type or style and/or represents the work of a significant landscape architect or designer"}
{"id": "4ba42682-5b0f-4732-b57a-43a79985e4ab", "value": "Access to the railroad through a spur track"}
{"id": "b7d89aed-1e8d-4b41-b9de-413068fdf73e", "value": "Double-hung windows, sometimes with hoods or pediments"}
{"id": "e0271df7-7dfd-465e-b233-0905b68477d2", "value": "Is associated with a women's club or organization that played a pivotal role in the social history of L.A. or a specific L.A. community"}

{"id": "dc95e3e5-1410-4184-bdab-42a6b6ac8021", "value": "Replacement of some windows and doors may be acceptable if the openings have not been resized and original fenestration patterns have not been disrupted"}
{"id": "bc4dd6bd-9c19-461a-83f2-4343d77b13ac", "value": "Is an excellent example of Late Modernism"}
{"id": "6b0cfc27-02c1-48b4-b7c0-1370e74d877b", "value": "May be jointly used/owned by city and county offices"}
{"id": "10698f96-40ae-40d4-a641-1f715968ced9", "value": "Hipped or gabled roofs, typically with boxed eaves"}
{"id": "0f36f7f4-01ad-4152-9e8d-11338778c0c4", "value": "Sprawling clusters of buildings connected by covered walkways"}
{"id": "65bbd1b0-a039-4d21-9dcb-3f1a23a3ac1b", "value": "Often bear signs on both sides and may include other intersecting shapes and forms that jut from the primary structure at different angles"}

{"id": "59dcaf2d-ab76-4e6b-abe2-5149b1e192cc", "value": "Concentration of numerous outbuildings fields, barns, stables, groves, yards, feed lots or other agricultural buildings and structures typically organized around a ranch house"}
{"id": "d72f5f9e-e8e8-435b-a285-1addecad8558", "value": "Typically includes carefully graded and paved hardscape elements"}

{"id": "86a589cc-0dc9-4ad3-9c45-12efb4a63d8f", "value": "Associated styles: American Foursquare, Shingle, Craftsman, Art Deco, Spanish Colonial Revival, Mediterranean, American Colonial Revival, English Tudor Revival, French Revival, Classical Revival, Renaissance Revival, Mid-Century Modern, Traditional Ranch"}
{"id": "28f9cb16-141d-473b-82b7-8814519b1790", "value": "Should retain integrity of Location, Design, Material, Workmanship, and Feeling from its period of significance"}
{"id": "61892242-1e48-408c-a95b-7ec9904689a8", "value": "Fireproof construction with large interior assembly space using day-lighting"}

{"id": "23763fac-508d-404a-bcc3-32e0d121f79d", "value": "Low lot coverage, usually less than 20%, with buildings oriented around multiple courtyards or set within a larger landscape, a primary feature of the design"}
{"id": "89f7c74f-b400-4234-be15-ecdca3141934", "value": "Later examples may still be in use"}

{"id": "0b627a3a-940a-4b8a-a5f2-1f83b8fc9c89", "value": "If constructed before 1940, may include continuous, oversized industrial sash; extensive skylights; and sawtooth, butterfly, Aiken, or monitor roofs"}
{"id": "b9ce42a0-c14a-4797-9af4-7d38c76a7502", "value": "May represent a distinct lighting type specifically designed for a community/area"}

{"id": "b0e161b8-4fb9-48d2-af5a-0cb3c428c772", "value": "Within districts, the threshold of integrity for contributing properties is defined as the ability of a particular building to reflect the architectural style and form that it would have possessed at the time of construction"}
{"id": "0ff51acd-f355-4593-a150-54660e7fb6dd", "value": "Applied decoration may include finials, medallion or other ornament"}
{"id": "ddb18cae-75ad-4b8e-807f-3dc018d7bae7", "value": "Must be proven to have played a significant role in agricultural development for local and/or regional/national markets"}
{"id": "253686ab-e1ef-4e73-b66c-a987a425c8be", "value": "Original streetscape features, such as street trees and lights, may be missing in limited amounts"}
{"id": "2c7cca76-ace5-4602-a439-e5fef3df84a2", "value": "As a whole, retains cohesiveness as a planned community"}
{"id": "fa6dcf08-fb34-4188-897b-a04026c88844", "value": "Is associated with a person who made important individual contributions to commercial growth and development"}
{"id": "ab81bde9-883f-4d3b-a65c-cbdb4ad5471d", "value": "Is a neighborhood significant for its role in fighting/ending deed restriction relating to racial segration"}
{"id": "e1542993-0977-447a-94c2-3524f6145447", "value": "Retains the essential character defining features of the Late Hollywood Regency style from the period of significance"}
{"id": "1ab145bc-7f1d-472e-bc28-9e820bc29f40", "value": "Developers known for creating distinctive or innovative suburban design concepts may also be considered a \"master\" under Criterion C"}
{"id": "4a942c63-8f68-40a6-a611-37f9d3dacdb4", "value": "Multi-gabled and conical roof forms with no or shallow overhanging eaves"}
{"id": "a72fa284-cbd2-4b66-a862-9bb2787c0036", "value": "Association is not a required aspect of integrity for determining historical or architectural significance as the use may have changed"}
{"id": "fd0022f0-3202-4cd5-8d4c-e0bf747b915b", "value": "Oriented towards major thoroughfares, often at an angle, sometimes not corresponding to the current formal street address or main entrance"}
{"id": "36099b84-e675-4b6e-b3b8-06214b6578cd", "value": "May include civic-themed areas such as a parade ground or pavilion for outdoor performances"}
{"id": "a880441c-599f-4576-8c24-f2e5e3031ff5", "value": "Most are installed on a building, traffic light, or a freestanding support pole"}
{"id": "48c09fc4-d496-4ec3-9f27-d9f3bc27a886", "value": "May also be associated with a related retail repair shop"}
{"id": "2c19dcce-10d5-4b0e-ab02-e29345e4ddd6", "value": "Commercial uses may include retail, office, banking"}

{"id": "b1c7492d-3aa3-417a-ad87-557b39a3d434", "value": "May exemplify design features of Art Deco, Streamline Moderne, exaggeratedly modernist/\u201cGoogie,\u201d or thematic architectural styles\u2014streamlines, angularity, offset composition of intersecting forms, fanciful or programmatic pictorial illustrations"}
{"id": "fdb7e66d-0a80-411f-85cf-dab1f7a88aef", "value": "Proximity to other produce markets, cold storage warehouses, and rail spurs"}
{"id": "02614248-483e-4ead-9973-c9f878fdb41d", "value": "Extant examples of this property type are extremely rare"}
{"id": "1c49a531-9ccd-452f-907e-d03bb80808c0", "value": "May represent issues relating to equal access to education or school desegregation"}
{"id": "d5d68aec-2844-48dd-b8b9-814ac3066d58", "value": "Narrowly proportioned double-hung windows, often with bordered glass"}

{"id": "30620985-bce8-463b-94ab-a5683fdf952a", "value": "If the only remaining resource associated with the person, may be eligible even if all/most of the significant work occurred before living in the property"}
{"id": "edba060d-7e15-4d0f-8c3e-a6fe5f99d0f9", "value": "Ground floor with storefronts and large display windows; openings remain intact"}
{"id": "6b6991b7-6107-49ff-a80f-9b5e98876207", "value": "For local preservation, sign may have been moved off site to avoid demolition, for parallel use elsewhere, or for artistic display"}
{"id": "9c77e992-4851-4f34-8b6e-e743cd790183", "value": "May also be significant under themes within the Architecture context"}
{"id": "d464afd4-1c5b-427d-a39a-efc87a6831a4", "value": "Represents an early or rare example of the style in the community in which it is located"}
{"id": "1686909d-b921-4b7c-b09b-f7a81d4d0de1", "value": "Often designed in architectural styles of the period"}
{"id": "5751a460-246e-4d4e-9e9f-1337019feddf", "value": "Cornice may have been removed to comply with seismic regulations"}
{"id": "48a46a2a-ca8f-4a36-9d08-9931413a86f7", "value": "The physical relationship between the area and the motion picture studio may still be apparent"}
{"id": "cb5f9834-419a-43c5-a259-26535e74e0cf", "value": "May contain some buildings from outside the period of significance"}
{"id": "6d023580-821c-41c1-bd6e-6cf2eaeacba0", "value": "Flat roof, often with heavy, projecting overhang"}
{"id": "d11dcb27-968c-45f8-b6e3-844c62590442", "value": "Exemplifies the tenets of the late Victorian era and the Folk Victorian style"}
{"id": "559c9252-6f58-4519-aee5-fe3145e5a3ae", "value": "At least two stories in height, but typically taller"}

{"id": "e4715bd1-890c-40aa-8571-8d62cf855ef3", "value": "Loss of some original plant buildings, tanks or towers may be acceptable provided there are sufficient structures on the site from the period of significance that represent the process of refining and compressing natural gas"}
{"id": "416eeff9-bed0-414e-be75-ac1a5dbe2392", "value": "Fenestration in the front and rear generally multi-light sash"}
{"id": "b2fabd03-e8c8-428f-8056-41b9519e34a4", "value": "Represents an important association with an ethnic/cultural group or groups in Los Angeles"}
{"id": "592d128a-332f-4166-8066-468d746a44bd", "value": "May serve as a prototype for mass-produced corporate or chain-store logos"}

{"id": "dcb79ddf-5b3f-496c-b403-a0746cd04e40", "value": "Open landscape with agricultural features that may include a farm house, farm land, orchard/grove, agricultural outbuildings and related features such as corrals, irrigation systems, standpipes, and tanks"}
{"id": "fec66a29-f95d-4c89-9368-143735948218", "value": "For local HCM may have been relocated within Hollywood for preservation purposes"}
{"id": "f52ea317-b537-4ee3-b790-7fdc04aa955e", "value": "Divided into multiple storefronts which open directly to the sidewalk"}

{"id": "222b115c-e946-4cba-ad89-30a7cd6dcb8a", "value": "Evokes iconic cultural associations with period- or regionally specific commercial establishments, personae, or multiple-family residential properties, and/or is an excellent example of an architectural style or promotional technique from its period"}
{"id": "f45fa718-11c8-410d-b1d2-3c650db46d39", "value": "Use of regionally appropriate plants and/or native species"}

{"id": "c5d20932-8ab4-439f-ae0d-ce414bac7f36", "value": "Unified entity with a significant concentration of residences designed in Arts and Crafts styles including Craftsman, Tudor Revival, Prairie, American Foursquare, and American Colonial Revival"}
{"id": "e0d21dd3-41fc-4130-99da-1bf3cda290e6", "value": "May be associated with ethnic, cultural, women\u2019s or LGBT groups"}
{"id": "ed5cfb99-5114-467a-b5d9-317a9acc1112", "value": "May be used for a different tenant or industy than that for which is was originally developed"}
{"id": "5d0f9f1f-941d-40cc-b679-5a9879decb60", "value": "Is associated with the 1947 and 1955 municipal bond measures"}
{"id": "5f486bc5-3736-48a4-bef4-e985b4ff966d", "value": "Is an excellent example of the Early American Colonial Revival style"}
{"id": "39ff68b3-ac68-4848-b39f-c95ea49fdac7", "value": "May include limited use of vegetation, moveable furniture, potted displays, earthwork, and berms"}
{"id": "e93d5ef0-e3d5-4c4e-a780-422b96187a2d", "value": "Design elements such as compartmentalized beds, terraces linked by stairs, hillside engineering, fountains, and statuary"}
{"id": "a9c2d509-ab53-49dc-9079-43dce466ad38", "value": "Ornamentation often rendered by cut-out patterns, drilled holes, and thin, layered wood with sharp edges"}
{"id": "e08a0bd4-14b9-42f2-b0c6-371ac6d2367f", "value": "May be associated with an important movement in education history"}
{"id": "d4b28877-c97a-46bc-ae07-a5fec0728732", "value": "Retains industrial infrastructure and streetscape including railroad spurs, loading docks, and brick or granite swales"}
{"id": "7be8e040-e935-410a-8b33-8b9cb626a049", "value": "May be overgrown with plants and trees"}
{"id": "189911f5-a236-4af6-bc7a-b7d12ec27955", "value": "Processing activities generally include canning, breading, and smoking"}
{"id": "e72c33b6-fa24-401a-9669-6c732667986a", "value": "May include industrial, commercial, and/or converted residential buildings"}
{"id": "f882465c-5c89-40d6-b1ce-dfc36b0fe60b", "value": "Includes a substantial concentration of intact small-scale buildings which form the commercial center for a neighborhood or community"}

{"id": "0ec92051-aa1f-4336-ac13-3aeba73d8634", "value": "Was constructed immediately following the establishment of the facility or facilities that provided entertainment-related jobs (e.g. motion picture studio and industrial support centers)"}
{"id": "ac966c95-58c4-4999-9fe2-b9dfb0c9dede", "value": "Some are formed in the sheet metal of fascia or cornices or painted above the fascia"}
{"id": "c8935db5-a44e-4bfc-9946-fd1f9f216b35", "value": "Planting schemes may be selected to enhance local ecological systems"}
{"id": "bf0876f7-e7dc-47ab-aa63-b88fdef9127d", "value": "Security bars may have been added to ground level"}
{"id": "da7b62c2-53be-481a-a472-6f65d79527d1", "value": "Was originally constructed as an apartment tower"}
{"id": "ce14e992-1d4c-449b-812d-4333fde002fa", "value": "May also be significant under a Modernism theme within the Architecture context"}
